                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1171-2">AMS, II, 397-441 ; BHO, 177.
Hoffmann, Auszuge, 17- 19.
Suhadii', I, 291- 306.
DHGE, VI, col. 477 (A. van Lantschoot) , avec references, et toute Ia litterature sur
le couvent rassemblee dans Assyrie chretienne, II, 565- 613.
H. Younansardaroud, "Die Legende von Mar Behnam", in M. Tamcke, ed. , Syriaca
(Wittenberg, 2002), 185- 96.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="dates" source="#bib1171-2"/>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1171">Behnām and his sister <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2063">Sara</persName> were high-born Christian martyrs who
          were the children of Sennacherib. They converted to Christianity through a monk, Mattai,
          and were killed by their father. Their father later repented and became a Christian and
          with his wife Queen Shirin. Sennacherib and Shirin built monasteries for Mar Mattai and
          Abraham near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/139">Mosul</placeName>.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">goes with Sara</note>
